  <description><![CDATA[<p>Thanks to its cliff side spot on <a data-udi="umb://document/af2f016e6c4f412b9ddb75ba9495d88f" href="/{localLink:umb://document/af2f016e6c4f412b9ddb75ba9495d88f}" title="Island of Ischia">Ischia</a>’s west coast, everything from the thermal pools to the rooms at the Continental Mare look out over the island-speckled Gulf of Naples. This family-run property is an ideal choice for those looking for a relaxing escape. Pastel colours decorate the welcoming communal areas and the hotel is surrounded by a large, quiet park. However, you’ll find Ischia’s port just a short, pleasant walk away.</p>
<p>Guest rooms are comfortably decorated and you can upgrade to a sea view for wonderful views of the Gulf of <a data-udi="umb://document/3f78d09ffda249fe84dca900e9fedde9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f78d09ffda249fe84dca900e9fedde9}" title="Naples">Naples</a> from your balcony. The restaurant serves up Mediterranean fare using local ingredients, while the expert bar staff pour long fruit cocktails and Riserva wine.</p>
<p>For those here to experience Ischia’s famous geothermal water, the Continental Mare offers a free shuttle bus to the spa at the Hotel Continental Terme. Treatments here include nourishing volcanic mud masks and massages.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 40 mins by private car and hydrofoil/ferry from Naples Airport</p>]]></description>
